{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3184c6e9-fdd5-456b-b7e6-a8c46e9226f6","content":"Here's the analysis of **EvalHeavy.csproj** — three evaluation performance anti-patterns found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. 🔴 Expensive Wildcard Glob (line 9)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the **entire directory tree**, matching every file with an extension. This is extremely costly in large repos (especially with `node_modules`, `.git`, etc.). **Fix:** scope the glob to specific extensions/directories, or add broad exclusions via `$(DefaultItemExcludes)`.\n\n### 2. 🔴 File I/O During Evaluation (line 13)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n`System.IO.File::ReadAllText` performs **disk I/O during project evaluation** — one of the most expensive property function patterns. Every evaluation (IDE load, build, restore) pays this cost. **Fix:** move this to a target that runs at execution time, or use a build task to read the file.\n\n### 3. 🟡 Chained Import Depth (line 6)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nA **3-level deep import chain**. Currently modest, but this pattern scales poorly — each level adds evaluation overhead. **Fix:** flatten into a single `.props` file when possible.\n\n---\n\n**Highest impact fix:** the `**\\*.*` glob and `ReadAllText` property function — these dominate evaluation time and run on every IDE/build interaction.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cac2ed2a-2ff7-45a9-a4ff-e94fccd23375","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze it for MSBuild evaluation performance issues.\n\nThe issues I can identify:\n\n1. **Expensive glob pattern**: `<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />` - This is a very broad glob that walks the entire directory tree. It matches every file with an extension, which is extremely expensive in large directories. It would also pick up files in `node_modules`, `.git`, etc. if they existed.\n\n2. **File I/O property function during evaluation**: `$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))` - This reads a file during evaluation, which is expensive. File I/O during evaluation should be avoided.\n\n\n3. **Deep import chain**: The props files are nested three levels deep, with each import adding overhead to the evaluation phase. While not extreme, this pattern can compound as the project grows.","outputTokens":682,"requestId":"7818:1BEBDD:1E63E09:22D05DF:69F551BB"},"id":"cd741a4b-9b2e-4ed9-978d-f92a1677938f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:22:18.685Z","parentId":"c1ba9c68-059f-4bad-b4f8-93eb5080a2be"}
